%
		    Files in the ITRANS/lib directory
            -----------------------------------------------------
                    http://www.aczoom.com/itrans/
            -----------------------------------------------------

% $Header:$

itrans.sty		-- LaTeX style file, can be used standalone,
			   or with latex2html

htmlstub.sty		-- ITRANS/doc/*.itx files use html.sty from 
			   latex2html, if you don't have latex2html installed,
			   change the docs to use htmlstub.sty instead

DVIPSRC			-- sample .dvipsrc file
			-- should reside in user's home directory with
			-- name .dvipsrc
			-- On PC's should be name dvips.ini
			-- See the documentation on DVIPS in the DVIPS package.

SHENV			-- sample lines to add to your .profile/.login etc
			-- Needed by TeX or by itrans itself
			-- On the PC, add similar lines to your autoexec.bat

FONTS.SCALE		-- sample lines to add to your fonts.scale file
			-- this file should be renamed & moved to the
			-- ITRANS/lib/fonts directory, and users should then
			-- run "mkfontdir" and then "xset fp+
			-- ITRANS/lib/fonts" to let X11 know where to load
			-- these fonts from.

itrans.map		-- the psfonts.map lines that need to be appended to
			-- the systems psfonts.map
			-- For the PostScript fonts - devnac, scguj, bvbeng

--------- Devanagari

idevn.tex		-- some useful TeX/LateX macros for writing
			   devanagari using Devnag or Devnac font.

dvnc.ifm		-- devnagari font metric file, used by itrans
			-- to map transliterations in devnagari
			-- (hindi/marathi/sanskrit)
			-- For Devnac PostScript font

dvng.ifm		-- devnagari font metric file, used by itrans
			-- to map transliterations in devnagari 
			-- (hindi/marathi/sanskrit)
			-- For Devnag Metafont font
dvngfull.ifm		-- devnagari font metric file, used by itrans
			-- to map transliterations in devnagari
			-- For Devnag Metafont font, contains many archaic
			-- conjunct forms, may be useful for sanskrit/pali
			-- writers.

xdvng.ifm		-- For the Devnag font used with Jtrans
			-- Can be used to generate text that can be 
			-- displayed using WWW HTML browsers.

udvng.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Telugu

tlgutx.ifm		-- telugu font metric file, used by itrans
			-- For the telugu font from the TeluguTeX
			-- package - available at the usual FTP sites.

itrnstlg.tex		-- definitions of special telugu chars/accents
			-- For the telugu font from the TeluguTeX
			-- package - available at the usual FTP sites.

tikkana.ifm		-- for conversion of sanskrit ITRANS docs to
			   telugu script using Tikanna fonts

utel.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Kannada

kantex.ifm		-- Kannada font metric file, used by itrans
			-- For the Kannada font from the KannadaTeX
			-- package - available at the usual FTP sites.

ukan.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Tamil

wntml.ifm		-- Washington Tamil indian language font metric
			-- file.
			-- Metafont font (for TeX).

--------- Gujarati

itxguj.ifm		-- ITRANS IFM file for ItxGuj Gujarati font

uguj.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Bengali

itxbeng.ifm		-- ITRANS IFM file for ItxBeng Bengali font

bnbeng.ifm		-- ITRANS IFM file for BWTI Bengali font

ubeng.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Gurmukhi

pun.ifm			-- ITRANS IFM file for 'Punjabi' Gurmukhi font

ugur.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Romanized Sanskrit (CSUtopia -- modified Adobe Utopia font)

romancsx.ifm		-- ITRANS IFM file for the CSX Roman Sanskrit fonts

uroman.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Oriya and Malayalam (Unicode output only)

uoriya.ifm		-- For Unicode output

umal.ifm		-- For Unicode output

--------- Font Files (TeX Files, and Display fonts for PC/Mac/X11)

Directory:
	.../ITRANS/lib/fonts 	All the *.mf, *.pfa, *.tfm, etc font files
	See the README file in that directory.

